race.comment: POLO (8) well-bred filly with a fitness edge over the bulk of these fifth-up. Relished the jump in trip when a close-up fourth over 1600m at Kembla Grange. Winkers go on and will prove hard to hold out. RIDGEBACK (2) tagged the good tempo on resumption when a plugging second over 1500m at Hawkesbury. Strips fitter and gets map favours around this course. LIKE ANYTHING (6) went back from the outside gate on resumption when a plodding eighth over 1500m at Kembla Grange. Can race closer from the better draw and play a leading role. MAMMA MIA (7) at her top for this and should have little trouble getting the mile. Strong through the line when second over 1400m at Nowra. Will need luck early from the gate. Keep safe. STOCK ROAD (3) will push forward and run a much better race with Berry sticking. Value chance.
